default7.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFEDOMA’s long
default standing efforts to engage the media to raise the issue of rights
default of disabled persons bore fruit when journalists in a national newspaper independently uncovered that disabled children were taught in rooms previously used as toilets in a school in Blantyre, Malawi. The media outlet gave the story a lot of coverage and t
defaulthe reaction was immediate. The local member of Parliament got engaged and even the mobile provider Zain initiated a text message campaign to its customers which spread the story nationwide. After initial reluctance on the part of the local authorities and 
defaultheadmaster of the school, the children were moved to a new and bigger classroom on the same premises. 
defaultThe partners in this project are FEDOMA and NAD.
default&#xa0;
default7.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Microfinance and Disability Project in Uganda aims for disabled persons to enjoy equal and fair acce
defaultss to quality financial products and services. The project is doing targeted lobby and advocacy activities towards a selected segment of microfinance institutions in Uganda and also training of economically active men and women with disabilities. This has 
defaultresulted in close collaboration with the Center  for Financial Inclusion at ACCION where ‘disability’ has become a new dimension in financial inclusion
default;
default increasingly inclusive microfinance institutions
default;
default and disabled persons being awarded as outstanding entrepreneurs. On a personal 
defaultlevel,
default disabled persons are able to provide for themselves and their families, gaining independence and a sense of self-worth while at the same time contributing to the economy
default.
default The partners in this project are NUDIPU, AMFIU and 
defaultNAD
default.
default&#xa0;
default7.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe CBR program implemented by MACOHA in Malawi is working to promote more inclusive practices in local communities to improve the access of disabled children and adults to their
default rights, entitlements
default and available services and to increase their participation in their communities.  CBR workers and District CBR Committees report that their efforts to raise the awareness of local magistrates and chiefs on the rights of disabled perso
defaultns are 
defaultachieving 
defaultresults.  After encouraging these local leaders to practice an inclusive justice system, an increasing number of disabled persons, many of whom are women, have reported violations of their rights.  Raising awareness about the right of disa
defaultbled persons to earn a livelihood has resulted in local chiefs including disabled persons in all public works projects.  For example, in the Traditional Authority Somba in Blantyre district, after many years of exclusion, it is now a familiar sight to find
default disabled people among those clearing a road and receiving fertilizer or cash for their work.  
defaultThe partners in this project are
default              
defaultMACOHA, the 
defaultpara-statal organization in Malawi
default that 
defaultimplements the CBR program
default, and NAD.
