default7.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultT
defaulthe Rehabilitation Program in 
defaultPalestine
default, which 
defaulth
defaultas 
defaultCBR 
defaultas its 
defaultcornerstone,
default has recently implemented a 3-year project aimed at contributing to increased promotion and protection of the rights and entitlements of 
defaultdisabled 
defaultchildren and adults from the Arab-Palestinian community in East Je
defaultrusalem.   As a result of action taken by lawyers acting within a legal framework to secure the rights of disabled persons in East Jerusalem, the Israeli Ministry of Transportation has committed to making the three central bus terminals in East Jerusalem a
defaultccessible by 2014 and has agreed to expand the number of bus lines that will ultimately be made accessible.
default The partners in this project are Bizchut (an Israeli disability rights organization), 
defaultthe EU, 
defaultDiakonia and NAD.
